             was indicted for a <rs id="t18250915-349-off1891" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18250915-349-off1891" type="offenceCategory" value="royalOffences"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-349-off1891" type="offenceSubcategory" value="coiningOffences"></interp>
               like offence
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-349-victim1766" type="victimName">
                  WILLIAM 
                  DAVIS
               <interp inst="t18250915-349-victim1766" type="surname" value="DAVIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-349-victim1766" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-349-victim1766" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-349-off1891 t18250915-349-victim1766"></join>
                  </persName>
            . I am servant to Messrs. Wilson and Co. of <placeName id="t18250915-349-crimeloc1892">King's Arms-yard, Coleman-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-349-crimeloc1892" type="placeName" value="King's Arms-yard, Coleman-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-349-crimeloc1892" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-349-off1891 t18250915-349-crimeloc1892"></join>. On the <rs id="t18250915-349-cd1893" type="crimeDate">1st of August</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-349-off1891 t18250915-349-cd1893"></join>, the prisoner came and asked if I had any old clothes to sell; I agreed to sell him some for 1 l. 9 s. 6 d., he gave me 9 s. 6 d., and said, he would owe me 1 l. - he then gave me two half crowns, then took them back again, and said, he would bring me 1 l. - he returned in half an hour, and gave me eight half-crowns; I looked at them slightly, and he went away; I examined them again, they seemed to sound odd - I left three with Hicks, and went out, and overtook him in Sweeting's-alley; he was running slowly with clothes on his back, and three hats - I stopped him, and took him back; he said, "Are you going to get me into trouble for nothing - do not send for an officer;" I had told him, I would expose him, for it was scandalous; I gave him in charge with the eight half-crowns.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-349-person1767">
                  RICHARD 
                  HICKS
               <interp inst="t18250915-349-person1767" type="surname" value="HICKS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-349-person1767" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-349-person1767" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am servant to Messrs. Wilson and Co. I examined these eight half-crowns; I saw that two were bad; Davis left three with me - he returned in about five minutes with the prisoner - we found in all that four of the half-crowns were bad.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. BRODRICK. Q. Did you put the three into your pocket? A. No. I did not examine them very minutely.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-349-person1768">
                  WILLIAM 
                  MACKAY
               <interp inst="t18250915-349-person1768" type="surname" value="MACKAY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-349-person1768" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-349-person1768" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a cellarman. I saw the prisoner running out of King's Arms-yard, at a very rapid rate - I pointed out to Davis, which way he ran.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-349-person1769">
                  JOHN 
                  ELLIS
               <interp inst="t18250915-349-person1769" type="surname" value="ELLIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-349-person1769" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-349-person1769" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a constable, and took the prisoner in charge. Davis gave me eight half-crowns; the prisoner said, "I will defy you to find any bad ones;" I said, there was; he said, "You may find one, but not more;" I said four were bad; he said, he took them in change for a sovereign, of a stranger in the street, of one of our people.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. He meant Christian? A. Yes; I found a few half-pence in his pocket, and in his left hand, four half-crowns, and two shillings, all good.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-349-person1770">MR. FIELD</persName>
            . Four of these are counterfeits, and of one die.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18250915-349-verdict1894" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18250915-349-verdict1894" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 23.</p>
